UPI FRAUD

UPI fraud is a common cybercrime in India where attackers trick people into sending money through fake payment requests or scam links.
Usually, the fraudster contacts the victim through phone calls, messages, or social media and pretends to be a bank officer, seller, or customer support agent. They may ask the victim to scan a QR code or approve a payment request. Once the victim accepts the request, money gets transferred from their bank account.
Students and people who frequently use online payments are often targeted because they may not be aware of these scams.
The consequences include financial loss, stress, and sometimes loss of personal data. In many cases, victims realize the fraud only after the money is gone.
Awareness and careful verification before making payments can help reduce such incidents.
